main event: A pilot and captain observed a bright, rapidly flashing white light while flying in an aircraft near Eveleth, Minnesota in 1962.
interesting points: The object appeared much faster than satellites previously observed by the witnesses,The object was observed from an altitude of 35,000 feet and faded out before reaching the horizon,The observation lasted for about 1 minute and 30 seconds,The witnesses were identified as Lieutenant Tomlinson and Captain Nelson from the 179th ANG and are considered reliable,Two F-102 aircraft were performing practice intercepts, but they were not mistaken for the reported object.
witness description: LT. Tomlinson (Pilot) and CAPT. Nelson from 179th ANG
